ð1aÞ

where ai is a ‘random’ shift in the intercept applying to both twins in pair i and eij is the usual individual-specific random error, and each of these is modelled as normally distributed
(independently of each other), with zero mean, and variances s2a and s2e , respectively. This model is completely equivalent to the alternative specification

